\subsubsection{Hello World in Erlang}
In 1805 Gottfried Llantwit-Major \cite{BookB} produced the first Erlang
version:

\begin{verbatim}
-module(hello).

-export([hello/0]).

hello() ->
   io:format("Sut dach chi?", []).
\end{verbatim}

Although this is very good attempt, as the reader will observe, it produces
Welsh output. Unfortunately however, it does not translate correctly to 
Hello World.

